****CASTING CALL** for girls ages 9-12 to STAR in short film**

**Union Status: **SAG-AFTRA Student Film

**Location: **Los Angeles / Orange, CA - MUST BE local hire, as there will be chemistry read and rehearsals before the shoot dates.

**Rate:** $125/day

**Dates:** Feb 13-15 and Feb 20-22, 2025

**Seeking:** Hispanic, Asian and White girls, ages 9-12. 

The girls are the stars of this film.

Submit headshot, resume and any reels to **submit.mirandacasting@gmail.com**

items.text:
Bright Star Touring Theatre is currently seeking actors for our 2-person national tours. We are accepting performers from all backgrounds including Hispanic, Black, and Indigenous actors. We are casting numerous shows including: ‚ÄúAlice in Wonderland‚Äù, ‚ÄúThe Wizard of Oz‚Äù, ‚ÄúWe Can Do It: A Celebration of Women‚Äôs History‚Äù, and ‚ÄúDino Academy‚Äù, a brand new show with realistic dinosaur puppets!

This is a paid opportunity, including a compensated rehearsal period, with travel and lodging provided for the duration of the contract. There is availability from January 2026 through Spring of 2026. Compensation is set at $450/week, with a $50/week bonus upon completion of the tour.

Applicants should have professional theatre training and experience (a theatre degree is preferable), a valid driver's license, as well as a clean driving and criminal record. We are currently only accepting applicants who are 21 or older. We are looking for strong character actors who are self motivated, independent, and want to travel to exciting, new places!

Please submit your headshot, resume, and availability to casting@brightstartheatre.com to be considered. We will be conducting virtual auditions via Zoom.

items.text:
Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

PS. Please note this is a university funded production and due to guidelines I am not allowed to pay anyone for their time. Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

**Casting Needs:**
**Male Singers (MS1/MS2)** ‚Äî tenor and high baritone roles with contemporary repertoire; some MS1 roles require basic rap performance.

**Contract Info & Requirements:**
‚Ä¢ STCW certification (or willingness to obtain)
‚Ä¢ Seafarers medical (ENG1 equivalent or MSC PEME)
‚Ä¢ Required vaccinations (Yellow Fever, MMR, Varicella)
‚Ä¢ Seaman‚Äôs book for Panama‚Äëregistered vessels
‚Ä¢ Contract durations typically 5‚Äì8 months

If you‚Äôre an experienced performer seeking international cruise opportunities, find more details and submit your application at **EvoqueHub.com** or by emailing your materials to **[auditions@evoquehub.com](mailto:auditions@evoquehub.com)**.

AUDITION ANNOUNCEMENT - URGENT! 

**UNPAID** 

AUDITION NOTICE ‚Äì Curious Incident of the Dog in the Nighttime, adapted by Simon Stephens, based on the novel by Mark Haddon.

Directed by Roger Beaumont for The Questors Theatre.

Performances Friday, 20th March ‚Äì Saturday 28th March 2026 

The Questors Theatre, W5 5BQ London. 

Audition dates: 

Monday, 22 December, 2025, 7pm 

Tuesday, 23 December, 2025., 7pm 

About the play:

‚Äò*Curious''* tells the story of 15-year-old neurodivergent Christopher Boone, who investigates the death of a neighbour's dog, and uncovers a web of lies that leads him to discover his mother is alive, not dead as he was told, and that his father killed the dog. Overwhelmed by his father's deception, Christopher runs away to London to live with his mother, a journey that involves navigating a terrifying and confusing new world. The play ends with Christopher taking and passing his A-level maths exam in London, showing he can achieve anything he sets his mind to, and beginning to repair his relationship with his father. 

Christopher experiences ‚Äòsensory overload‚Äô when exposed to unfamiliar places and situations and finds it hard to express his emotions, even to his parents. He also struggles to understand facial expressions and body language. He excels at maths and sciences and like his hero, Sherlock Holmes, relies on logic to make sense of the world around him. 

Character: 

1M late teens to mid twenties - Christopher 

Please email me on robinsonfeatures@gmail.com if you'd like to attend. 

An amateur production by arrangement with Concordetheatricals

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì STUDENT SHORT FILM üé¨

**UNPAID**

Hey everyone! I‚Äôm currently casting for my upcoming short film, *After the Rain*, an intimate emotional drama about two sisters navigating the aftermath of their mother‚Äôs sudden death. When a violent storm forces Mia and Isla back together, unspoken grief and buried pain rise to the surface, pushing them toward understanding, healing, and renewed connection.

To be shot in: High Wycombe/ London 

**Synopsis:**

After their mother‚Äôs sudden death, two sisters are pulled apart by grief, distance, and unspoken pain. Mia, the older sister, leaves to pursue a promising job opportunity, trying to outrun the heartbreak of their loss. Isla stays behind, sinking into isolation and self-destructive behaviour as her distress deepens. When Mia returns on a stormy night to find Isla drunk and unravelling, the sisters are forced to confront years of buried resentment and abandonment. Through raw confessions and shared vulnerability, they begin a journey towards understanding, forgiveness, and the possibility of hope, finding solace in the quiet strength of sisterhood. 

Characters:

**ISLA (19-22, FEMALE)** 

impulsive, reckless, emotionally unstable little sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and intoxication.  

**MIA (25-28, FEMALE)**

protective, compassionate, responsible older sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and the effects of grief. 

Shooting: DATES TBC  (approx JAN 6-16th)    

If interested, please contact me for more information at austenfilmworks@gmail.com 

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested. üé•üé¨

URGENT-

Looking for a couple of performers available 23rd & 24th December in the Herts/Beds/Bucks area. Both dates 10am-4pm.

Non-speaking elf role, super silly and fun, physical improv lead. You will be working in a pair travelling to several different locations throughout the day. The other elf can drive so as long as you can get to a meeting point, driving isn't necessarily needed. 

Costume provided, no accommodation (looking for local people). Would suit students home for Christmas with an interest in acting and performance, and a whole lot of Christmas cheer! 

Pop me a message for further info ASAP. ‚ù§Ô∏è

This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

items.text:
Marketing Macabre - a horror public relations company created to give independent filmmakers an affordable alternative. We focus on the importance of publicity to gain momentum and we work with some of the biggest genre websites in the world. Our mission is to get your project in front of your audience, the horror public - the most devoted fan base in all of entertainment.   

Our enhanced filmmaker services will supply you with everything needed on your cinematic journey from pre-production to post-production to distribution.  We have forged relationships out of trust and loyalty with partners that stretch from Hollywood studios to distribution companies.   In the evolution of horror, we have evolved from a marketing company to something more.  

A creation born out of necessity and a genesis into a one-stop-horror-shop that offers not only marketing, but opportunities in brand development, film funding, and distribution.  There are many complexities of making a feature film but our marketing militia will guide you on your journey and be your source to access the horror multiverse that is Marketing Macabre.

Casting Homebuyers in and around the Greater Toronto Area! 

Hi! My name is **Jessica McGann**, and I‚Äôm a Casting Producer for a *brand-new* MEM real estate series that celebrates homebuyers stepping into one of the most exciting chapters of their lives.

If you‚Äôve recently purchased a home, recently moved in, or you‚Äôre actively on the hunt ‚Äî I‚Äôd love to hear your story!
* Homebuyers will be needed for 5 ‚Äì 6 days of filming 
* Filming begins spring 2026  
* An honorarium and special perks will be provided to those selected  
* It‚Äôs a fun way to commemorate and celebrate this new chapter of your life! 

üëâ Apply here: [https://homebuyers.castingcrane.com/](https://homebuyers.castingcrane.com/)

Hey everyone! Dan Bell Casting is seeking children ages **13‚Äì17** or adults **60+** to participate in a paid face-capture research study with a major social media platform.

The goal is to improve their facial filters. It pays **$350** for approximately **2.5 hours** of participation in **Los Angeles**.

If interested, please sign up using the form below:
[https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc_IIH7UC8Wl8QtqqpDkonbDSU24SHMFnQqKFL5CoE3ay7jJA/viewform](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc_IIH7UC8Wl8QtqqpDkonbDSU24SHMFnQqKFL5CoE3ay7jJA/viewform)

(Please keep in mind that this does involve the use of **AI facial scanning**, so please do not sign up if you are not comfortable with that.)

I've participated in the study myself and was able to complete it in an hour! Feel free to check out our Instagram @danbellcasting or call the office if you have any questions.

Hey everyone! Dan Bell Casting is seeking children ages **13‚Äì17** or adults **60+** to participate in a paid face-capture research study with a major social media platform.

The goal is to improve their facial filters. It pays **$350** for approximately **2.5 hours** of participation in **Los Angeles**.

If interested, please sign up using the form below:
[https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc_IIH7UC8Wl8QtqqpDkonbDSU24SHMFnQqKFL5CoE3ay7jJA/viewform](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc_IIH7UC8Wl8QtqqpDkonbDSU24SHMFnQqKFL5CoE3ay7jJA/viewform)

items.text:
FREE HEADSHOT with any of my packages - my Christmas gift to you.

Book a session by Christmas (for a headshot session in the New Year) and I‚Äôll include one extra headshot completely free.

I guide you throughout the shoot to help you feel comfortable and to create a strong range of headshots that help you stand out and get noticed by casting professionals.

We‚Äôre looking for fabulous new faces to join A Roman Rumble ‚Äì The Rude Panto, touring across Yorkshire, Nottinghamshire and beyond from November 2026 to January 2027.

We‚Äôre casting:

  2 x Roman Guards ‚Äì male chorus, ideal for newcomers

 ‚Ä¢ 3 x Female Chorus ‚Äì market traders, handmaidens etc.

2 x lead male roles - villainous sidekick & silly boy

We welcome all backgrounds, body types & experience levels. Must be up for a laugh, willing to sing & dance (badly is fine!) and give it your all.

This is unpaid, volunteer work ‚Äì just like the rest of us. We do it for the love of it, not the money. All income goes back into making the show more brilliant and bonkers each year.

We‚Äôve been proudly described as ‚Äúabhorrent satire masquerading as pantomime.‚Äù

We call it mega fabby ace brill.

Email me to find out more 

Faroutrachael@gmail.com

30 min Short Film / Proof-of-concept pilot Episode (Graduation Project)

We are casting PAZUZU, a supernatural entity in a dark, poetic fantasy-horror pilot.

Age: Open (25s‚Äì40s)

Gender: Open

Location: Berlin

Production: Independent / Graduation Project

Compensation: Unpaid, meals + credits + content for showreel.

Shooting days: January 19 - 24 

Pazuzu will require 2 shooting days. 

Pazuzu is not a traditional demon.

He is intelligent, unstable, and addicted to souls, not out of cruelty, but desperation. He is caught

between cosmic power and emotional decay.

This role requires:

‚óè Strong presence and restraint

‚óè Comfort with psychological intensity

‚óè Ability to shift between charm, menace, humor, and vulnerability

‚óè Voice and stillness are as important as physicality

If interested:

Please email for self-tape instructions to

celia.t@catalyst-students.com

items.text:
Hi everyone!

My theatre group Thalia‚Äôs Tantrums Theatre Company has an online series that we do each year. This is our third year and we‚Äôre starting 2026 off with an actor based series ‚ÄòThe Midweek Monologue Series‚Äô in January. As this is an online series the time would be 7pm PT. However we are going to hold a showcase performance (held in Vancouver,BC) and I thought that if people wanted to showcase a monologue they always wanted to do, it could be screened alongside the live (Vancouver based) performances. 

This is a non paid project for us all, just to work on monologues and hopefully network etc. so if you wanted to take part we would screen your monologue (and provide any socials/ website info) and get you some follows/ showcase your talents.

For more info, please email thaliastantrumstheatreco@gmail.com

Or check out our website/ socials for the main notice (this is however geared for people who would be in the online session).

Dieses Erkl√§rvideo (KI generiert) ist ein Auszug, vielleicht eher eine verk√ºrzte Zusammenfassung, des Buches "HAGIA SOFIA, Siehst Du noch den Wei√üen Turm", und enth√§lt sowohl narrative Kapitel als auch umfangreiche Quellenangaben und formale Abschnitte. **PAID** Hi everyone! We are currently casting for WISP, a haunting coming-of-age drama about isolation, queer longing, and the grip of an unseen presence.

To be Shot in: West Yorkshire.

 

Synopsis:

Sixteen-year-old Noah has spent weeks drifting from everyone he loves,

manipulated by an unseen presence. When his best friend Sam turns up on New Year‚Äôs Eve, Noah finds himself caught between feelings he‚Äôs long buried and the Voice that refuses to let him go.

 

Characters:

NOAH (16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Quiet, introspective, emotionally guarded. Must be able to convey internal conflict, subtle fear, and vulnerability with restraint.

SAM (16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Warm, intuitive, and grounded. Noah‚Äôs best friend; emotionally open, present, and deeply human.

 

Shooting: 12/2 ‚Äì 15/2   (Night Shoots)

Payment: TBD ‚Äî we are happy to discuss this with you.          

 

üì© Contact: [jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com](mailto:jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com) with Showreel if available. Script will be available.

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested.  üå≥üñ§

## **üé≠ Casting Breakdown: *****OUROBOROS***

A Psychological Horror film. The Fourth Film from Pineal Dreams Productions.

‚ÄúWhen a young couple suffer the pain of a miscarriage; they retreat to a cottage in the woods to try and heal. Unfortunately they quickly discover that you can never run away from your trauma‚Äô

**DONN**

**Male | Playing age: 30-40 | Ethnicity: Open**

**Description:** Amaia‚Äôs partner. Kind, supportive, but emotionally shut down. A man attempting to cope through suppression - a misguided attempt at stoicism as he believes she must be strong to support Amaia - whose quiet unraveling becomes key to the resolution.

 **Performance notes:** Understated emotionality. Requires physical performance (injury, crawling, etc.) and strong presence in silence.

 **Comparable roles:** Michael Fassbender (*Shame*), Mads Mikkelsen (*Another Round*), Javier Bardem *(Mother!)*, Harry Dean Stanton *(Paris, Texas)*

Filming block will be the same as Amaia‚Äôs. Five-day block (Hopefully), as well as shoots at just three other locations.Ten days of filming maximum, but this could always change if re-shoots are necessary, and one day of ADR work will be required.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**üë• Supporting Roles -**

**THE UMBRA**

**Male | Playing age: ANY | Tall, slender, distinctive presence | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A silent manifestation of trauma that watches over and manipulates events ‚Äî a mythic observer of Amaia‚Äôs trauma. Symbol of death, memory, or fate.

 **Performance notes:** No dialogue for a vast majority of the script, though requires a sequence of some very carnival-esque dialogue. Face never seen. Must convey gravitas, mystery, and quiet threat through stillness and gaze.

 **Type:** Dancer, mime, or physical performer backgrounds welcomed. Could even opt for the possibility of a physical performer, and a separate voice-actor. So any voice-actors interested, please feel free to contact us.

Similar Roles: Doug Jones (Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth), Tim Purcell (The Babadook), Javier Botet (Slenderman)

The Umbra appears in the Cottage and scenes surrounding it, all of which will be filmed during the scheduled five-day filming block.

There will also be one additional day, in which you will be required for a single scene that takes place in a different location.

Re-shoots are of course always possible, and will be needed for one ADR session for dialogue provided during an animated sequence.

PAID - But a smaller fee than Amaia/Donn as will be required for less days.  This can be discussed upon application. We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with one scene needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require tsix days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

We are a very small studio, and this is our fourth short. However, our mantra has always been a ‚Äòquality over quantity‚Äô approach. We take great pride in not just making a film, but really thinking it through on a technical level. We appreciate classic and arthouse cinema, and are far more interested in making a good film than red carpet events.

Our three shorts so far have been screened at over 20 festivals, picking up around 14 awards - including two IMDB qualified awards. (best actor for Jackson Wright in Inside The Abyss). Our latest film has seen our lead - Tash Morley - pick up three awards. We aim for this to be our best film yet.

If interested in the roles, please contact me directly via the Pineal Dreams Instagram page. My own personal profiles - both Joshua Moulini√© (Facebook/Instagram). Or Email me directly on [Moulinie23@gmail.com](mailto:Moulinie23@gmail.com)

We hope to hear from you all very soon!

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì MOSH PIT / GRUNGE GUYS**

**Date: **Mon Dec 22

**Platform:** TikTok / Reels / Short-form video
**Role Type:** Mosh Pitt BG
**Age:** 21-35
**Location:** Warehouse
**Compensation:** $100 per hour

We're looking for 8x grunge-looking guys to be part of a short-form shoot. The music artist will be performing with 8x of you being shot having fun behind him. **This should only take an hour, max two hours.** We are looking for someone reliable, professional and someone who is looking to have fun.

**WARDROBE:**
Simple, all black. No markings / logos. More direction to follow after being casted.

**HOW TO APPLY:**
Email or DM:
* Name + age range
* Location
* Recent photo
* **Short selfie video (15‚Äì30 sec) introducing yourself**

**Perfect Xmas Gift for Actors! *****‚ÄúTHE ACTOR'S MANIFESTO: Create a Successful Acting Career‚Äù*** Amazon Books--blends techniques, neuroscience, psychology, and industry business savvy to help actors master the craft and the industry.

**What it covers:**

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

The Business: Advice on navigating the entertainment industry.

Science: Neuroscience on how acting works in the brain.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

 

Written by Linda Ann Watt, SAG-AFTRA, AEA Member, SAG-AFTRA Signatory Producer/Director, MFA in Theatre Pedagogy, and 2015 Tony Award Nominee for Education. This book bridges theory and the demands of an acting career. **TheActorsManifesto.org**

Ist es f√ºr dich auch Zeit? Dich wahrhaftig zu zeigen, unverwechselbar zu sein, deine Seele und deine Essenz ins Schauspiel einzubringen?

## christmas time at The Three Crutches, 
##                       A traditional family-friendly pub

Ditzy, Sparkle and Tiny spread the Christmas cheer and Santa descended to The Three Crutches today. 

Located on the outskirts of Cobham woods on the scenic drive into Higham village, The Three Crutches provides a cosy respite from exploring the village and surrounding natural landscape. With local walks starting from their doorstep into the picturesque countryside, a welcome haven after a day exploring so sit back, relax and indulge in delicious food with your favourite drink in hand.

Merry Christmas everyone!

With 2026 right around the corner The Audition Pal are thrilled to be announcing our first 2026 workshop- and it‚Äôs a big one 

Sophie Pearson Casting will be hosting a Zoom workshop on the morning of 17th January (GMT). 

Here‚Äôs a Bio on Sophie Below:

Sophie started her career working as an associate for Ros and John Hubbard, where she worked on projects such as ‚ÄúJourney‚Äôs End‚Äù (Directed by Saul Dibb), ‚ÄòThe More You Ignore Me‚Äô (Directed by Keith English), and ‚ÄòTime of Our Lives‚Äô (Directed by Roger Goldby). She then worked at Des Hamilton Casting, where she cast noteworthy ventures like ‚ÄúHilma‚Äù (Directed by Lasse Hallstr√∂m), the Netflix sensation ‚ÄúTop Boy,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe King‚Äù (Directed by David Mich√¥d), ‚ÄúJojo Rabbit‚Äù (Directed by Taika Watiti), and ‚ÄúMy First Film‚Äù (Directed by Zia Anger). Since starting Sophie Pearson Casting, Sophie has worked on many projects including ‚ÄòVows‚Äô starring Sarah Parish and Eddie Marsan and ‚ÄòThe Man With The Urn‚Äô starring Ciaran Hinds, Olga Kurlenko and Stephen Fry. Sophie is also working alongside Dan Hubbard Casting, on projects such as the TV series ‚ÄòThe Gentleman‚Äô (directed by Guy Ritchie) and ‚ÄòThe Rage‚Äô (directed by Paul Greengrass).

We are so excited for this one! So DM us on the platform or email us at: theauditionpals@gmail.com

# **CASTING CALL!!!**

We are casting for a new tour of the children‚Äôs theatre show, ‚ÄúTom Gates Live‚Äù, based on the popular book series by Liz Pichon.

The show is written and directed by Miranda Larson with songs and music by Barrie Bignold and is produced by Mark Thompson at MT Productions.

Rehearsals begin on 19th January ‚Äì 29th January 2025 in London.
Tour dates Jan ‚Äì Oct 2026. We are currently have 65 tour dates and counting. 

# **ROLE: Tom Gates**

Tom Gates is an easily distracted and creative 10-year-old boy who loves doodling, listening to music, and annoying his older sister, Delia.

He is best friends with Derek, and they share a passion for music, with dreams of becoming rock stars in their band, DogZombies.

We are looking for a musical theatre performer that can sing, perform slapstick and comedy, and can perform the role of a young boy.

Within the show, there is basic singing, dancing and movement but nothing too technical.

 

The successful applicant will need to be comfortable assisting with the load ins/ outs and have a full UK drivers licence as they will be asked to assist driving the touring van

Playing age: 16 years - 23 years

Gender: Male

**Contract info:**

Rehearsal fee: ¬£550pw

Show day fee: ¬£150

Travel day fee: ¬£50

Subsistence: ¬£20

Please send cv's and headshots to casting.mtproductions@gmail.com

Gesang, der ber√ºhrt. Geschichten, die verwandeln.

Die preisgekr√∂nte S√§ngerin Stefanie Rummel 

Ein Abend voller Gef√ºhl, Humor und internationalem Flair

Adresse: Gallus Theater, Kleyerstr. 15, 60326 Frankfurt, T:758060-20
Ticketverkauf:¬† https://www.gallustheater.de/prog/vob.php?i=27

www.chansons.show

20.02-04.03.2026 @adlfringe 
19.-21.03 @NewcastleFringe

 -------------------

SONGS FROM LIFE ‚Äì January 10, 2026 / 
Singing that touches. Stories that transform.
German Premiere

Award-winning singer Stefanie Rummel takes the audience on a captivating musical journey ‚Äì from the caf√©s of Paris to the cabaret stages of Berlin and the clubs of Manhattan.
With songs in the style of Piaf, Weill, Sondheim, as well as her own compositions, she tells stories of life‚Äôs special moments ‚Äì full of longing, humor, warmth, and depth.
Celebrated as ‚Äúheart-touching‚Äù and praised for her ‚Äúbrilliant stage presence,‚Äù she enchants audiences in the USA, the UK, and across Europe ‚Äì and will return to Australia on tour next year.

‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ ‚ÄúOutstanding voice‚Äù ‚Äì TheReviewHub
‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ ‚ÄúA revelation‚Äù ‚Äì LondonTheatre1
An inspiring, moving musical cabaret about life ‚Äì shaped by songs, personality, and storytelling.

Bernhard Lehner accompanies masterfully on piano.
Seven songs are written by Stefanie Rummel (lyrics & music). These songs were produced in collaboration with Tom Schl√ºter (pianist & music producer).

An evening full of emotion, humor, and international flair

S√∏ges: Cinematographer/kameramand til kortfilm der skal optages henover sommeren 2026. Ul√∏nnet.

Da jeg g√•r med en lille vision om at bryde ud som director efter flere √•r som skuespiller i tv og film branchen. Har jeg endelig f√•et skrevet en af mine mange historier f√¶rdig, men da jeg gerne vil bryde lidt med normen s√• skiller dette projekt sig ud da det bogstaveligt er en silent montage film, sat til klassikeren "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi. 

Vores working title er indtil videre "The Mafia burial".
Filmen vil vare ca 20min og og vil indeholde en del slow motion og koreograferede blodige action shots. 

Kort synopsis: En respekteret Mafia boss har mistet sit et og alt, nemlig hans datter. Historien starter p√• en kirkeg√•rd hvor vi overv√¶rer hendes begravelse, med en hysterisk gr√¶dende mor, en masse s√∏rgende h√•ndlangere og mange kondolerende g√¶ster. Iblandt h√•ndlangerne st√•r vores hoved karakter. Da vi zoomer t√¶ttere p√• ham ser vi ham smide en lille t√•re, det der skiller ham ud er dog at det er mere en bare sorg vi kan se i ham, han er lige s√• knust som familien da han var datterens hemmelige elsker. Da vi zoomer mere ind p√• ham breaker vi over i hans tanker i form af en montage. Hvor vi ser ham eliminere og afh√∏re flere kriminelle i jagten p√• hans k√¶restes morder. Alt dette vil lede op til begravelsen. Der vil komme sm√• brud imellem hans voldelige handlinger hvor han sl√•r over til de sm√• gode k√¶rligheds stunder han havde med hende.

Der skildres imellem en tone af film som The Godfather og Drive. 

Da det hele basically er en silent movie s√• har vi ogs√• valgt at tage os ekstra god tid til at finde de helt rigtige skuespillere til projektet da der her udelukkende skal arbejdes med udtryk og mimik. 
Musikken som vil drive filmen vil v√¶re et mix af "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi samt nogle andre klassiske stykker. Det hele skydes rundt omkring i Midtjylland men laves til at ligne et m√∏rkt amerikansk drama. 

Dette er et komplet passion projekt s√• det hele er ul√∏nnet. Men der vil v√¶re forplejning og god stemning p√• alle set.

Action scener vil v√¶re koreograferet og vi arbejder efter et koncept hvor vi pr√∏ver at f√• s√• meget som muligt ud af s√• lidt som muligt mht til vinkler close ups and so on. 

Vi begynder f√∏rst at kigge efter skuespillere n√•r det rigtige crew er fundet. Men skulle man falde over det her og t√¶nke at det er lige noget for mig s√• er man mere end velkommen til at skrive til os. 
Men i f√∏rste omgang ledes der efter en kameramand der selv har det n√∏dvendige udstyr og som kan se vores vision. Gerne med henblik p√• et fremtidigt samarbejde til flere produktioner i fremtiden. S√• hvis det evt er dig s√• smid en email til:

brook_lynmarvin@hotmail.com

Deadline for ans√∏gning er 1/3.2026

Projektet laves mht til at det skal vises p√• diverse film festivaler. S√• hvis man g√•r og br√¶nder for optagelse og editing og har lyst til at pr√∏ve at lave noget anderledes s√• er det her m√•ske projektet for dig.

items.text:
**CASTINGOPSLAG ‚Äì KORTFILM ‚ÄúALT I INTET‚Äù**

Vi s√∏ger **skuespillere i alderen 18‚Äì23 √•r** til hovedrollerne i vores kommende **ul√∏nnede kortfilm** *Alt I Intet*.
**Forplejning vil v√¶re inkluderet under optagelserne.**
Projektet har ambitioner om festivaldeltagelse og √∏nsker at skabe et v√¶rk, der kan n√• ud til et bredere publikum.

**Om projektet**

*‚ÄùAlt I Intet‚Äù* er et karakterdrevet drama, der unders√∏ger temaer som k√¶rlighed, sorg og identitet. Filmen bev√¶ger sig i gr√¶nselandet mellem virkelighed og erindring og skildrer en ung mands indre rejse efter et stort tab.

**Om os**

Vi er tre unge filmskabere med en f√¶lles passion for at skabe st√¶rke fort√¶llinger og ambiti√∏se filmiske v√¶rker med fokus p√• stemning, f√∏lelser og karakterudvikling.

 

**Roller**

**Oliver (mand, 18‚Äì23 √•r)**
Oliver er en ung, f√∏lsom og reflekterende mand, der er dybt knyttet til sine relationer. Udadtil fremst√•r han stille og n√¶sten anonym, som om han bev√¶ger sig gennem hverdagen p√• autopilot. Han lever prim√¶rt i minderne om sin afd√∏de k√¶reste, som fortsat p√•virker hans hverdag og selvforst√•else.

**Emma (kvinde, 18‚Äì23 √•r)**
Emma er en varm, n√¶rv√¶rende og livlig ung kvinde, der form√•r at se Oliver, n√•r han ikke selv kan. Hun repr√¶senterer b√•de k√¶rlighed, tryghed og det liv, Oliver har mistet.

 

**Logline**

Fortabt i minderne om Emma genoplever Oliver sit tab p√• gr√¶nsen mellem virkelighed og hallucinationer, indtil et m√∏de mellem liv og d√∏d giver ham et nyt blik p√• sig selv ‚Äì og p√• det liv, der stadig venter.

 

**Optagedatoer**

**L√∏rdag d. 7. marts ‚Äì s√∏ndag d. 8. marts**

**L√∏rdag d. 14. marts ‚Äì s√∏ndag d. 15. marts**

 

**Vigtig information**

Da filmen behandler temaer som k√¶rlighed og sorg, vil der indg√• semi-intime scener, herunder kram, h√•ndholdning og t√¶t fysisk kontakt.

For den kvindelige rolle forekommer der enkelte scener i badet√∏j. Disse scener har ingen seksuel karakter og vil blive behandlet med respekt og tydelig kommunikation.

 

**Ans√∏gning**

Vi ser gerne, at interesserede sender f√∏lgende:

**Selftape**

**Portr√¶tbillede**

**Alder og h√∏jde**

Ans√∏gning og eventuelle sp√∏rgsm√•l kan sendes via:
**E-mail:** magn715c@gmail.com
**Messenger: **Undertegnet

Vi ser frem til at h√∏re fra jer.

 

**Venlig hilsen**
**Magnus Petersen**
Producer ‚Äì ‚Äù*Alt I Intet‚Äù*

items.text:
''They got me an apartment in New York!''

She was close to tears on our zoom call.

''And the flight's paid for too! I even get a per diem of $100 a day! 
That's on top of what they pay me and it's A LOT, KC!''

After she got over the thrill of booking a recurring role on a series (in NY!!!) her mind was blown about everything else that came with it. 

She'd put almost 5 years of constant study with me to get to this level and she took absolutely none of it for granted. 

It was a lot of work and the work didn't stop when she got to NY. 

18 hour days.
Incredibly challenging scenes (I wish I could tell you because it's mind-blowing what she did but I can't).
Living in a country where she knew no one.

An since that series she's continued to work hard and book. 

It doesn't get easier when you find success. The challenges are different. 

You can start now and put in the work and build the muscles that help you meet those challenges. 

Or you can look back in 5 years from now and think I wish I did it. 

Regret is an ugly thing to live with. 

I have a few, but as the song goes, too few to mention. 

Donna-Marie Manning and I are very selective about who we work with. 

Your success is our success. 

We don't have these stories to tell if you don't book. So we only want to work with committed and dedicated actors.

When you fill out this form tell us everything. 

https://form.jotform.com/253125203574248

We promise we won't laugh at you or judge you for wanting to act. 

We know people sometimes do. We don't. 

Our job is helping actors make their dreams come true. 

Don't hold back. We need to know you to coach you. 

xo KC

With 2026 right around the corner The Audition Pal are thrilled to be announcing our first 2026 workshop- and it‚Äôs a big one 

Sophie Pearson Casting will be hosting a Zoom workshop on the morning of 17th January (GMT). 

Here‚Äôs a Bio on Sophie Below:

Sophie started her career working as an associate for Ros and John Hubbard, where she worked on projects such as ‚ÄúJourney‚Äôs End‚Äù (Directed by Saul Dibb), ‚ÄòThe More You Ignore Me‚Äô (Directed by Keith English), and ‚ÄòTime of Our Lives‚Äô (Directed by Roger Goldby). She then worked at Des Hamilton Casting, where she cast noteworthy ventures like ‚ÄúHilma‚Äù (Directed by Lasse Hallstr√∂m), the Netflix sensation ‚ÄúTop Boy,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe King‚Äù (Directed by David Mich√¥d), ‚ÄúJojo Rabbit‚Äù (Directed by Taika Watiti), and ‚ÄúMy First Film‚Äù (Directed by Zia Anger). Since starting Sophie Pearson Casting, Sophie has worked on many projects including ‚ÄòVows‚Äô starring Sarah Parish and Eddie Marsan and ‚ÄòThe Man With The Urn‚Äô starring Ciaran Hinds, Olga Kurlenko and Stephen Fry. Sophie is also working alongside Dan Hubbard Casting, on projects such as the TV series ‚ÄòThe Gentleman‚Äô (directed by Guy Ritchie) and ‚ÄòThe Rage‚Äô (directed by Paul Greengrass).

We are so excited for this one! So DM us on the platform or email us at: theauditionpals@gmail.com 

Here are the links to our free platform for Actors. Never pay or struggle for a read in for your auditions again! Join us if not on the platform already!

**NOW CASTING ‚Äì LA Based Gen Z Contestants for a Series of New Digital Game Shows!**

A major cable company‚Äôs digital channel is looking for Gen Z contestants for game shows in Los Angeles!

Contestants should be outgoing, competitive and looking to have fun. We are producing a series of different shows that will be centered around Gen Z trivia, physical competitions and dating ‚Äì so there is a show for everyone!

In your submission, please let us know if you are single and want to be on a dating game show. We are open to all genders and sexual orientations.

Also, let us know if you are a pro when it comes to sports or Bible trivia.

**Apply today by emailing**  d3gameshowcasting@gmail.com with the following information:

Name ¬∑ Phone Number ¬∑ Email Address ¬∑ Current Location ¬∑ Recent Photos ¬∑ Social Media Handles 

Filming will take place January 2026 in Los Angeles, CA. All applicants must be at least 18 years old, live in the LA area and be US Citizens or permanent residents of the United States.

items.text:
I recently had a detailed conversation with Kurt Evans of Artist2Artist, one of the established actor showcase platforms, specifically around demo reels, self-tapes, and how casting actually encounters actors.

A few points from that discussion are worth sharing, because they clarify a lot of confusion I keep seeing among actors at different stages.

On demo reels:
Casting directors are not ignoring traditional demo reels. A professional demo reel is still exactly that ‚Äî the professional work you‚Äôve done, compiled into a roughly three-minute video. What matters is how that reel is structured.

Rather than one or two long scenes, the reel works best when it‚Äôs made up of multiple 20‚Äì30 second sections, each clearly showing a type you would naturally be called in for ‚Äî parent, authority figure, professional roles, etc. The goal isn‚Äôt to replace the reel, but to make it immediately readable. Realistically, a director may only watch about 20 seconds before deciding whether you fit, so clarity matters more than length.

On highly produced self-tapes:
We spoke about the rise of very cinematic, highly produced self-tapes ‚Äî essentially mini-movies. Kurt isn‚Äôt against production value. In fact, he shared an example where one panelist loved a highly edited tape, while another felt it looked more like a finished production than an audition.

The key point he emphasized is that the purpose of a self-tape or showcase submission is still to evaluate acting. Most actors audition two to three times a week. It‚Äôs neither realistic nor necessary to shoot a short film every time. What casting needs is a clear window into the performance. Overproduction isn‚Äôt a mistake ‚Äî it‚Äôs just not what casting is primarily judging.

On agents and casting access:
This is the part many actors misunderstand. Casting primarily encounters actors through agents. It‚Äôs not about gatekeeping or access ‚Äî it‚Äôs how the system functions. There‚Äôs a trust relationship between agents and casting offices.

In a traditional setting, a casting assistant may block off hours of time, receive hundreds of short submissions from agents, and narrow those down to about twenty strong fits. That‚Äôs how casting begins to connect with talent. Without representation, casting offices often have no way of knowing an actor exists.

What showcases like Artist2Artist aim to do is create a space where casting can watch actors work outside the volume and time pressure of the standard submission pipeline.

The takeaway from the conversation was straightforward:
For actors who want to be seen consistently in film and television, representation is the first gateway into that ecosystem.

Award-winning singer Stefanie Rummel takes the audience on a captivating musical journey ‚Äì from the caf√©s of Paris to the cabaret stages of Berlin and the clubs of Manhattan.
With songs in the style of Piaf, Weill, Sondheim, as well as her own compositions, she tells stories of life‚Äôs special moments ‚Äì full of longing, humor, warmth, and depth.
Celebrated as ‚Äúheart-touching‚Äù and praised for her ‚Äúbrilliant stage presence,‚Äù she enchants audiences in the USA, the UK, and across Europe ‚Äì and will return to Australia on tour next year.

**CASTING & PARTICIPATION CALL ‚Äì MADE FIGHT LEAGUE‚Ñ¢ REALITY SERIES (LAS VEGAS)**

Made Fight League‚Ñ¢ is officially recruiting for an upcoming **6-week unscripted reality series** filming in **Las Vegas** in **early 2026** (exact dates TBA).

We are hiring **both UNION and NON-UNION** talent.

This project blends **entertainment, comedy, drama, lifestyle, and competition** inside a **safe, professionally run environment**. It will be **streamed 24/7**, capturing real personalities, real moments, and real opportunity.
WHO WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR:

‚Ä¢ Actors (union & non-union)
‚Ä¢ Everyday people with strong personalities
‚Ä¢ Athletes & fighters
‚Ä¢ Musicians & artists
‚Ä¢ Comedians & entertainers
‚Ä¢ Creators, performers, and big characters
‚Ä¢ Anyone who believes their **experience, resources, or credit** could meaningfully support production is also encouraged to reach out
KEY DETAILS:

‚Ä¢ **Location:** Las Vegas
‚Ä¢ **Duration:** 6 weeks
‚Ä¢ **Ages:** 21‚Äì45 (must be 21+)
‚Ä¢ **Status:** Paid, role-based participation
‚Ä¢ **Travel & lodging:** Provided
‚Ä¢ **Daily per diem:** Provided
‚Ä¢ **Environment:** Safe, professional, fully managed
‚Ä¢ **Format:** Unscripted reality (entertainment, comedy, drama)
‚Ä¢ **Exposure:** Major visibility through Made Fight League‚Ñ¢ platforms

This is a **career-level opportunity**, not a hobby project. The right participants will gain exposure, content, connections, and real momentum.
HOW TO APPLY:

Email **madefightleague@gmail.com**
**Deadline:** **January 10th**

Please include:
‚Ä¢ A short description of who you are
‚Ä¢ Why you‚Äôd be a strong fit
‚Ä¢ Photos **or** social media links (Instagram preferred)

If you‚Äôve ever wanted to be part of something **bigger than a one-off gig**, this is it.

Serious inquiries only.

‚Äî **Ashlee Gambino**
Co-Founder, Made Fight League‚Ñ¢

**Perfect Xmas Gift for Actors! *****‚ÄúTHE ACTOR'S MANIFESTO: Create a Successful Acting Career‚Äù*** Amazon Books--blends techniques, neuroscience, psychology, and industry business savvy to help actors master the craft and the industry in USA.

**What it covers:**

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

The Business: Advice on navigating the entertainment industry.

Science: Neuroscience on how acting works in the brain.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

 

Written by Linda Ann Watt, SAG-AFTRA, AEA Member, SAG-AFTRA Signatory Producer/Director, MFA in Theatre Pedagogy, and 2015 Tony Award Nominee for Education. This book bridges theory and the demands of an acting career. **TheActorsManifesto.org**

items.text:
Warmest Holiday Wishes from Our Creative Family to Yours!

As the season blankets Colorado and 2025 draws to a close, we at S.E.B. Casting, CSA want to take a moment to thank you for being part of our vibrant community of performers, directors, producers, advertisers, agents and creative visionaries. Your talent and passion continue to inspire us every day.

A Year of Breakthrough Performances
2025 has been extraordinary for the S.E.B. Casting community. From launching careers in award-winning productions to connecting diverse talent with innovative projects, we've watched with pride as performers have shined in everything from national commercials and viral ad campaigns to feature length films. Your commitment to authentic storytelling has helped productions across Colorado and beyond create more inclusive, powerful productions.

What's New at S.E.B.
We're thrilled to announce our studio expansion will be complete in January 2026! This means a more comofrtable audition space, improved casting facilities, and a dedicated area for talent and production. Plus, our Commitment to the Community will continue to grow, lifting individuals, groups. organizations and our whole state as a vibrant, positive, engaging, equitable hub for media arts and artists. 

Holiday Self-Care for Performers:
The holidays can be both magical and hectic for creative professionals. Here are our top tips to stay centered and ready for opportunities in the new year:

Schedule downtime: Block specific days for complete rest - no auditions, no rehearsals, no networking

Stay vocally healthy: Maintain your instrument with extra hydration and vocal rest during holiday gatherings

Update materials: Use the quiet period between December 20-January 5 to refresh headshots, reels, and resumes

Connect authentically: Attend industry gatherings not just for networking, but to genuinely celebrate the season with your creative community 

Here's to New Beginnings!
As we wrap up 2025, we're filled with gratitude for this remarkable community. The new year promises exciting productions, fresh opportunities, and continued growth for Colorado's vibrant media arts scene. Whether you're a seasoned professional or just beginning your journey, know that S.E.B. Casting, CSA is here to champion your unique voice and talent.
